data.name: textBoxDescription.Text
data.value:
Classroom Inquistion is the latest in classroom technolgy. It was developed by David Christensen during his senior year at Purdue University. It is meant not only to be incredibly useful but also intuitively simple. It is perfect for the students who are afraid of asking the "dumb" question, as well as the inquisitive student who interrupts normal class proceedings.
Feel free to contact the developer with any suggestions. God Bless, David Christensen
